</div>I don't see a problem with that -- about 80% of the data I administer is Public info.  It is freely given out (some with fees, some without - depending on the nature of the info &amp; the format etc) -- so even though there's no problem with me giving you the info -- there is a Problem if you circumvent my controls and take it, and should be charged.<br />
