<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				MIT and JSTOR are not pressing charges and not suing for damages.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Once a criminal complaint is made - it's up to the DA to press charges; the wishes of the victim are usually taken into consideration, but that's not a guarantee charges will or won't be pressed- whatever the crime.  <br />
as far as their suing for damages - their legal department probably noted that, while there is a loss there, the loss is minimal - and not worth the time to recover;  Or who knows, perhaps the DA suggested they wait on that pending the outcome of the criminal case --- if that settles with or without restitution - they can still sue for damages, if the restitution doesn't cover the full loss.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
