		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Activist Arrested for Hacking into MIT and downloading scholarly articles
				</h2>
				

						
						
							
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1693529">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							1. JSTOR should be freely available to anyone who wants it.  It should be available via a portal at any website for any public library or high school.  It's beyond stupid that anyone would prevent anyone from accessing JSTOR for any reason at all.  I've learned more about topics that interest me off of JSTOR searches over the past year than I've learned from the sum of every official college class I've taken over the course of that year.  &quot;Information wants to be free&quot;.<br />
<br />
2. What really pisses me off about this is that a guy like this gets indicted while for-profit organizations like the one I contract with do the same exact thing, take all that information, and repackage it and resell it.  Just what the hell is up with that?  Nobody's indicting the owners of the huge information data warehouses out there and believe you me they are doing the exact same thing this guy is doing with public records.  Where in the world are our priorities as a country... hell as a species?<br />
<br />
Edit:  it does already have and needs enforcement of the ol' &quot;cannot reproduce for monetary gain or without express permission of Major League Baseball' boilerplate, but that's about it.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
				<!-- edit note -->
				<blockquote class="postcontent lastedited">
<!--					<img src="images/buttons/edit_40b.png" class="inlineimg" alt="" /> -->
					
						Last edited by Grindel; July 20th, 2011 at <span class="time">08:48 AM</span>.
					
					
				</blockquote>
				<!-- / edit note -->
				
                                       
                                 
				
                                        
			</div>
			
